thread.title: VIDEO: Joey Logano, Kyle Busch leave Kansas victorious

author: Brandon Reed
title: VIDEO: Joey Logano, Kyle Busch leave Kansas victorious
text:
By Brandon Reed Reporter Joey Logano crosses the finish line to win Sunday's NASCAR Sprint Cup Series race at Kansas Speedway. Photo: Chris Trotman/NASCAR via Getty Images Related Articles Coby sweeps Thompson to win third Whelen Mod title Earnhardt must win Talladega after rough Kansas race Post Race Notes: Cut tire spoils run for Austin Dillon NASCAR Results 
Matt Kenseth appeared to be on his way to the NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory on Sunday, as he had led 153 laps at Kansas Speedway. But Joey Logano had other ideas. 
After the two jostled for the lead over the closing laps, Logano tagged Kenseth going into turn one with just five laps to go, sending Kenseth spinning and handing Logano his second straight Chase victory. 
It’s the fifth win of the season for Logano, who has locked other Chase contenders out of being able to safely transfer during the Contender round of the Chase. Afterwards, Logano said the incident was just hard racing. We also heard from car owner Roger Penske and second place finisher Denny Hamlin. 
Kyle Busch came back from a pit road penalty, damage to the front of his Toyota and a slow pit stop to power to his 75th career NASCAR Xfinity Series victory Saturday at Kansas Speedway. The win is the third of Busch's Xfinity Series career at Kansas and his fifth series win of the season. 
With 43 laps to go, Busch drove from seventh to second, then stalked teammate Matt Kenseth for 28 laps before driving to the lead and away for the win with 15 to go. Busch talked about the win afterwards. We also heard form second place finisher Kenseth. 
The NASCAR Sprint Cup Series heads for the unpredictable high banks of Talladega Superspeedway this weekend for the final race of the Contender round of the Chase for the Sprint Cup. WDUN will have MRN Radio live coverage of Sunday’s action beginning at 1 pm on 102.9 FM.
